according to the hebrew bible , " bat sheva , " more commonly known by the anglicized name bathsheba ( or ; , baṯ-šeḇa‘ , " daughter of the oath " ; , " ابنة القسم " ) was the wife of uriah the hittite and later of david , king of the united kingdom of israel and judah .

the bible : after seducing bathsheba , david plotted to have this man , her husband , killed in battle

uriah the hittite